help_10: Other than the  typical vehicle tracking, vehicle status, it is also integrated with vehicle maintenance system, Driver Behavior as well as it comes default with Cargo-Link system where owner  not only gets a truck but also gets a job.
help_11: How to view in Real-time tracking on map?
help_12: Click "Real Time Dashboard" from the left menu.  The overall status of My Vehicles and My drivers will show on the screen as Donut charts.  on the right, user will see summary Behavior score and if click "Maintenance Status" the sreen will replace behavior summary with maintenance status summary.  By scrolling down, user will see map with a list of vehicles on the right.  Click on any vehicle to see live status of each vehicles.
help_13: How to view Tracking History on Map?
help_14: Click "History" from the left menu, then select Vehicle from the right menu and click to select the history period to view.
help_17: How to view fuel tank level?
help_20: Click "Real Time Dashboard" on the left menu, then select vehicle number from the right menu, then drag scroll bar at the bottom to the right most till the maintenance box appears.

help_28: From main menu, click on your picture at the top-right cornner, the 'Change Password' box will appear.  Enter the current password, new password, confirm new password then click 'Submit' button.  You're done!
help_29: What is annual fee? How to pay annual fee?
help_30: It is annual fee to use Hino Connect product and service.  You will receive a bill from Onelink one month in advance indicating an amount to pay.  You can pay by using QR code or instruction given in the billing.
help_31: What is warranty for HINO CONNECT product?
